text: Schoenobius molybdoplecta is a moth in the family Crambidae. It was described by Harrison Gray Dyar Jr. in 1914. It is found in Panama.Schoenobius at Markku Savela's Lepidoptera and Some Other Life Forms The wingspan is 14–24 mm. The forewings are dark grey, the inner area shaded with dull yellow. The hindwings are whitish, shading to fuscous at the margin.Proceedings of the United States National Museum 47 (2050): 317 ==References== Category:Moths described in 1914 Category:Schoenobiinae
title: Schoenobius molybdoplecta
